       long getdtablesize(void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Each process has a descriptor table which is guaranteed to
       have at least 20 slots.  The  entries  in  the  descriptor
       table are numbered with small integers starting at 0.  The
       call getdtablesize returns the  current  maximum  size  of
       this table by calling the getrlimit system call.

